\frac{5x-7}{(x-2)(x-1)} = \frac{A}{x-2}+\frac{B}{x-1}
5x-7 = A(x-1)+B(x-2)
5 = A + B
-7 = -A-2B
A=5-B\\ -7= -(5-B)-2B\\ -2 = -B\\ 2 = B
A = 3
B=2
\int\frac{3}{x-2}+\int\frac{2}{x-1}=3\ln(x-2)+2\ln(x-1) + C
3\ln(2-x)+2\ln(1-x)
\int \frac{1}{u}\,du=\ln(|u|)+C
\frac{d}{dx}\ln(a-x)=\frac{-1}{a-x}=\frac{1}{x-a}=\frac{d}{dx}\ln(x-a)
